               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184809180096"></xptr>
               <p>was present on 4th April, 1836, at St. Mary's Church, Newington, when the prisoner was married to my sister, Elizabeth.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> When did you see her last? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Last night—the prisoner has kept two of my children for me, but one is dead—I may have told the Magistrate my name was Davis, and I was married.</p>
